metadata.name: The Elephant in the Dark
metadata.description:
Vector Art 2022
Uploaded size: 21x29.7 cm
Illustration based on an anecdote by Rumi

There was a group of Indians who, toured with their elephant from one town to another in places where no one hasn’t seen such a huge animal before. 
One day the Indians arrived at a new city’s gates after sunset. A nice family welcomed them and tethered the elephant in their stable. People soon heard about the newcomers and their exotic animal and couldn’t wait to see the show tomorrow at the city plaza. However, a handful of impatient folks wanted to be the first citizens to see the big animal, so they went to that house and insisted to see the elephant that night. "But there was no lamp in the stable and it is pitch black! " The Indian mahout warned them. So, they continued insisting, and eventually, the mahout agreed. immediately the nosy guys went through the stable and searched gropingly in the dark for the animal....
